# uv.toml.local.example
# Machine-specific uv overrides
#
# uv reads config from (in priority order):
#   1. Project-level: ./pyproject.toml [tool.uv] or ./uv.toml
#   2. User-level: ~/.config/uv/uv.toml (managed by this dotfiles module)
#
# Since this dotfiles module manages ~/.config/uv/uv.toml via stow,
# prefer these approaches for machine-specific settings:
#
# Option A: Environment variables (recommended for direnv/.envrc)
#   export UV_INDEX_URL=https://pypi.corp.example.com/simple/
#   export UV_EXTRA_INDEX_URL=https://pypi.org/simple/
#   export UV_CERT=/path/to/corporate-ca-bundle.pem
#   export UV_NATIVE_TLS=true
#   export UV_KEYRING_PROVIDER=subprocess
#
# Option B: Project-level uv.toml (per-project overrides)
#   Place a uv.toml in your project root. Project config takes precedence
#   over user config for keys that are set.
#
# All uv config keys can be set as UV_ prefixed env vars.
# See: https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/settings/
